{"questionId":"10121","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The function <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> is given by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f(x) = m{x^3} + n{x^2} + px + q\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span>, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m\">\n  <mi>m</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"q\">\n  <mi>q</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;are integers.</p>\n<p>The graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;passes through the point (0, 0).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The graph of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\">\n  <mi>f</mi>\n</math></span> also passes through the point (3, 18).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p class=\"indent1\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;\">Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"27m + 9n + 3p = 18\">\n  <mn>27</mn>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>18</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Attempting to substitute (3, 18)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"m{3^3} + n{3^2} + {p3} = 18\">\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mi>p</mi>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>18</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"27m + 9n + 3p = 18\">\n  <mn>27</mn>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>9</mn>\n  <mi>n</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>18</mn>\n</math></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG&nbsp; N0</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10121","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.8b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that 27 m + 9 n + 3 p = 18 .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}